S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINALS -- CORRECTIONAL INSTITUTIONS -- INTERSTATE
DETAINERS
Introduced By: Representatives Roberts, Quattrocchi, Place, Hopkins, Chippendale,
Fascia, Santucci, and Nardone
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: House Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 13-13 of the General Laws entitled "Interstate Detainers" is hereby
2 amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 13-13-9. Immigration detainers.
4 All state law enforcement agencies including, but not limited to, the division of sheriffs
5 and the department of corrections shall honor all detainer requests and any other holds from the
6 Department of Homeland Security and Immigration and Custom Enforcement. Any person with a
7 detainer request or other hold, of which the state agency has been made aware, shall hold said
8 person in custody until Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) can take custody of said
9 person.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
